In small saucepan melt butter over medium heat. Add mushrooms and whiskey; cook 8 minutes or until tender. Stir in flour and salt. Cook an additional 3 minutes. Meanwhile, spray 12-inch skillet with cooking spray. Heat over medium-high heat until very hot; add steaks. Cook steaks 7 to 9 minutes, or until desired doneness, turning once. Transfer steaks to clean plate and cover with foil for 5 minutes. Serve steaks with mushrooms.